	('PRJEB2733','SC','S.pombe is the \"other yeast\" genetic model system.  All 107 known wild isolates have been collected  around the world.  14 have already been sequenced.  The aim of the study is to sequence 96 samples (three overlapping with the previously sequenced 14) to generate a genetic diversity resource for S.pombe comparable to that available for  S.cerevisiae. This data is part of a pre-publication release. For information on the proper use of pre-publication data shared by the Wellcome Trust Sanger Institute (including details of any publication moratoria), please see http://www.sanger.ac.uk/datasharing/',NULL,'Germline','Control Set','Schizosaccharomyces pombe genetic diversity',4896),
	('PRJEB3025','IPK-Gatersleben','Variation data is shown from four cultivar (Barke, Bowman, Igri, Haruna Nijo) and a wild barley (H. spontaneum).','Leibniz Institute of Plant Genetics and Crop Plant Research (IPK), D-06466 Seeland OT Gatersleben, Germany; Leibniz Institute of Age Research- Fritz Lipmann Institute (FLI), D-07745 Jena, Germany','Germline','Control Set','Whole genome shotgun survey sequencing of Barley cv. Igri for de novo assembly of gene-space',112509),
	('PRJEB3027','IPK-Gatersleben','Barley (Hordeum vulgare L.) is amongst the oldest domesticated crop plants and remains one of the world\'s most important crop species. It is diploid with a haploid genome of 5.1 gigabases (Gb), twice the size of those of human and maize, and closely related to the most widely grown crop, hexaploid wheat. To meet global demand for food, feed and fibre, it is commonly agreed that reference genome sequences of our crop plants are urgently required to enable genome-assisted crop improvement. In the framework of the The International Barley Genome Sequencing Consortium (IBSC) we present here the whole genome shotgun rawdata of different barley cultivars and genotypes to build a physical ordered genetic and functional sequence resource.','Leibniz Institute of Plant Genetics and Crop Plant Research (IPK), D-06466 Seeland OT Gatersleben, Germany; Leibniz Institute of Age Research- Fritz Lipmann Institute (FLI), D-07745 Jena, Germany','Germline','Control Set','Whole genome shotgun survey sequencing  of Barley cv. Morex for de novo assembly of gene-space',112509),
